revision.text:
{{codepointer|Generic Attack}}
void '''A_RadiusDamageSelf''' [(int ''damage'' [, double ''distance'' [, int ''flags'' [, class<Actor> ''flashtype'']]])]

== Usage ==

Performs an explosive (radius) attack, much like {{c|[[A_Explode]]}}, that damages the calling actor's target only, which normally for [[projectile]]s, is their shooter.

While this function can be used by any actor, its usage should generally be restricted to projectiles only.

=== Parameters ===

*''damage'': how much damage is inflicted at the center of the explosion. Default is 128.
*''distance'': the area covered by the damage (damage inflicted drops linearly with distance). Default is 128.
*''flags'': customizes the behavior of the function<!--. Multiple flags can be combined by using the | operator between the constant names-->:
**'''RDSF_BFGDAMAGE''' â€” use the {{Class|BFG9000}} tracers' formula for damage. This works by picking and adding a random value from 1 to 8 a number of times which equals to the calculated damage over distance.
:Default is 0.
*''flashtype'': the actor to spawn at the target's position when damage is inflicted. This actor may have the {{Flag|PUFFGETSOWNER}}, {{Flag|FOILINVUL}} and {{Flag|FOILBUDDHA}} [[actor flags|flags]]. In addition, its {{c|{{Property|DamageType}}}} [[actor properties|property]] is used as the damage type of the attack. If this actor is not provided, the function defaults to {{c|{{DamageType|BFGSplash}}}} as the damage type to inflict. Default is {{c|null}}<sup>{{Zscriptfeaturesmall}}</sup>/{{c|"None"}}<sup>{{Decoratefeaturesmall}}</sup>.

== Examples ==

 class OddRocket : {{Class|Rocket}}
 {
     States
     {
     Death:
         MISL B 8 Bright [[A_RadiusDamageSelf]](72, 192.0, {{const|RDSF_BFGDAMAGE}}, "{{Class|BFGExtra}}");
         MISL C 6 Bright;
         MISL D 4 Bright;
         Stop;
     }
 }
